io.hekate.spring.boot.metrics.statsd

Class StatsdMetricsPluginConfigurer

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.hekate.spring.boot.metrics.statsd.StatsdMetricsPluginConfigurer

  • @Configuration
 @ConditionalOnHekateEnabled
 @ConditionalOnProperty(value="hekate.metrics.statsd.enable",
                       havingValue="true")
public class StatsdMetricsPluginConfigurer
extends Object
    Auto-configuration for StatsdMetricsPlugin.

    Module dependency

    StatsD integration is provided by the 'hekate-metrics-statsd' module and can be imported into the project dependency management system as in the example below:

    • Maven
    • Gradle
    • Ivy
    
 <dependency>
   <groupId>io.hekate</groupId>
   <artifactId>hekate-metrics-statsd</artifactId>
   <version>2.4.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
 </dependency>
 
    
 compile group: 'io.hekate', name: 'hekate-metrics-statsd', version: '2.4.0-SNAPSHOT'
 
    
 <dependency org="io.hekate" name="hekate-metrics-statsd" rev="2.4.0-SNAPSHOT"/>

    Configuration

    This auto-configuration is disabled by default and can be enabled by setting the 'hekate.metrics.statsd.enable' property to true in the application's configuration.

    The following properties can be used to customize the auto-configured StatsdMetricsPlugin instance:

    • 'hekate.metrics.statsd.host'
    • 'hekate.metrics.statsd.port'
    • 'hekate.metrics.statsd.batch-size'
    • 'hekate.metrics.statsd.max-queue-size'
    • 'hekate.metrics.statsd.regex-filters' - list of regular expressions to filter metrics that should be published to StatsD
    • 'hekate.metrics.statsd.name-filters' - list of metric names that should be published to StatsD
    See Also:
